COVID Flu: CITE-seq enriched genesets at baseline

Visualizing BTM 4.0/11.0 in monocytes and BTM 7.3 in CD8 memory cells at baseline

library(knitr)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(ggpubr)
library(RColorBrewer)
source('R/utils/visualization.R')

knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)
options(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
opts_knit$set(echo = TRUE, message = FALSE, warning = FALSE, cache.lazy = FALSE, out.width=900)
opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE, message = FALSE, warning = FALSE, cache.lazy = FALSE, out.width=900)

output.folder <- file.path("output","CITE-seq")
dir.create(output.folder)
## Warning in dir.create(output.folder): 'output/CITE-seq' already exists
figure.folder <- "figures"
dir.create(figure.folder)
## Warning in dir.create(figure.folder): 'figures' already exists

Data import

# cite-seq pbulk data
pseudobulk.list.filtered <- readRDS(file.path(output.folder,"covid_flu.CITEseq.pseudobulk.gene.expr.filtered.RDS"))
cat("Cell subsets:",names(pseudobulk.list.filtered))
## Cell subsets: B B_dblt B_Mem B_Naive B_Naive_Intermediate CD4 CD4_CM CD4_EM CD4_Naive CD4_platelet_bind CD4_Tfh CD4_Treg CD8 CD8_CM CD8_EM CD8_EM:GPR56hi CD8_EM:GPR56lo CD8_Naive CD8_proliferating CD8_TEMRA CD8_TRM cDC dblt gdT-Vd2 HSPC ILC Mac-or-Mono MAIT Mono Mono_Classical Mono_Intermediate Mono_NonClassical Mono-T-dblt Neut NK NK_CD16hi NK_CD56hiCD16lo NK_dblt NK_proliferating pDC Plasmablast Platelet
# read in all citeseq GSEA results
gsea.files <- list.files(file.path(output.folder,"GSEA"),pattern = "vaccine.response.gsea",full.names = T)
citeseq.gsea.results <- do.call(rbind,lapply(gsea.files,read.csv))
citeseq.gsea.results[,c("visit","contrast")] <- t(sapply(citeseq.gsea.results$term,stringr::str_split_fixed,"\\.",n=2))
citeseq.gsea.results$num.LE.genes <- sapply(sapply(citeseq.gsea.results$core_enrichment,strsplit,"/"),length)

Selected baseline enriched genesets

citeseq.baseline.genesets <- subset(citeseq.gsea.results,term %in% c("Baseline.COVR.f","Baseline.COVR.m") & P.Value < 0.05)

selected.depressed.genesets <- c("cell cycle and transcription (M4.0)","enriched in monocytes (II) (M11.0)")#,
                     # "OXIDATIVE_PHOSPHORYLATION")
mono_subsets <- c("Mono_Classical","Mono_NonClassical")

selected.tcell.activation.genesets <- c("T cell activation (II) (M7.3)")
CD8_mem_subsets <- c("CD8_CM","CD8_EM")

# merged plot
merged.baseline <- rbind(cbind(group="Monocytes",
                               subset(citeseq.baseline.genesets,parameter %in% selected.depressed.genesets & cell.type %in% mono_subsets)),
                         cbind(group="T-cells",
                               subset(citeseq.baseline.genesets,parameter %in% selected.tcell.activation.genesets & cell.type %in% CD8_mem_subsets)))
merged.baseline$contrast <- ifelse(merged.baseline$contrast == "COVR.f","COVR-F\nvs.\nHC-F","COVR-M\nvs.\nHC-M")

ggplot(merged.baseline,aes(contrast,cell.type)) + geom_point(aes(fill=NES,pch=NES > 0),color="black",size=4) + 
  ggforce::facet_col(~parameter,scales = "free_y",space = "free") + ylab("Cell type") + theme_bw() + 
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",legend.box = "vertical",strip.background = element_blank(),strip.text = element_text(size=7)) +
  scale_shape_manual(values=c(25,24)) + ggtitle("","CITE-seq cell subsets") + 
  scale_fill_gradientn(colors=colorRampPalette(c("#0066FF","#003399","#000066","black","yellow4","yellow"))(100))

TSD correlation of selected genesets

Take the union of LEGs in M4.0 and M11.0 to form sex-specific IIR signature in the two monocyte subsets

# LE genes
le.genes <- subset(citeseq.gsea.results, term %in% c("Baseline.COVR.f","Baseline.COVR.m") &
                     ((parameter %in% selected.tcell.activation.genesets & cell.type %in% CD8_mem_subsets) | 
                     (parameter %in% selected.depressed.genesets & cell.type %in% mono_subsets)))
le.genes <- le.genes %>% group_by(cell.type,contrast) %>% summarise(genes=strsplit(paste0(core_enrichment,collapse = "/"),"/"))
names(le.genes$genes) <- paste0(le.genes$cell.type,".",ifelse(le.genes$contrast == "COVR.f","Female","Male"))
le.genes <- sapply(le.genes$genes,unique)
saveRDS(le.genes,file.path(output.folder,"baseline.selected.LEG.list.RDS"))

# module scores of LE genes
citeseq.sample.info <- pseudobulk.list.filtered[["Mono_Classical"]]$samples
for (celltype in c(CD8_mem_subsets,mono_subsets)) {
  sample.signature.scores <- GSVA::gsva(pseudobulk.list.filtered[[celltype]]$normalizedExpr,
                                        gset.idx.list = le.genes[grep(celltype,names(le.genes))],
                                        parallel.sz=6,min.sz=5)
  citeseq.sample.info <- cbind(citeseq.sample.info,t(sample.signature.scores)[rownames(citeseq.sample.info),])
}

citeseq.sample.LE.scores <- reshape2::melt(citeseq.sample.info,measure.vars = names(le.genes))
citeseq.sample.LE.scores <- as.data.frame(citeseq.sample.LE.scores %>% 
  group_by(alt.subject.id,visit,group,sex,covid.diagnosis.start.date.to.sample.drawn,age,race,variable) %>% 
  summarize(module.score=mean(value)))

# separate into sex-specific scores for corresponding subjects
female.citeseq.sample.LE.scores <- citeseq.sample.LE.scores[grep("Female",citeseq.sample.LE.scores$variable),]
female.citeseq.sample.LE.scores <- subset(female.citeseq.sample.LE.scores,sex == "Female")
male.citeseq.sample.LE.scores <- citeseq.sample.LE.scores[grep("Male",citeseq.sample.LE.scores$variable),]
male.citeseq.sample.LE.scores <- subset(male.citeseq.sample.LE.scores,sex == "Male")
citeseq.sample.LE.scores <- rbind(female.citeseq.sample.LE.scores,male.citeseq.sample.LE.scores)
citeseq.sample.LE.scores$cell.type <- gsub("\\.(Female|Male)","",citeseq.sample.LE.scores$variable)

tsd.scatter.plot(subset(citeseq.sample.LE.scores,visit == "Day 0" & group == "COVR"),"module.score","cell.type") + 
  ylab("LEG module score") + facet_grid(sex~cell.type)
